    "body": "My reasoning is: with module-state / freethreading, static storage in functions makes me increasingly unhappy. Neither of those apply to PyPy or GraalPy yet so it's more future-proofing. I also think the number of people using the Python 2 iteritems/iterkeys/itervalues is increasingly low, so I don't really care about caching a string for their speed.\r\n\r\nAlso refactor the string comparison a bit to try to skip the common chunks.",
