                },
                "message": "Remove static PyObject* from PyPy/GraalPy __Pyx_dict_iterator\n\nMy reasoning is: with module-state / freethreading, static\nstorage in functions makes me increasingly unhappy. Neither\nof those apply to PyPy or GraalPy yet so it's more future-proofing.\nI also think the number of people using the Python 2\niteritems/iterkeys/itervalues is increasingly low, so I don't\nreally care about caching a string for their speed.\n\nAlso refactor the string comparison a bit to try to skip the\ncommon chunks.",
